events.text: [color=#ffed29](Alright, now that [tootroot] is taken care of, I got another call to do.)
[color=#ffed29](Sigh, I’m not sure if I want to see anyone right now.)
Look at you, all fully grown! You look amazing!
Your lettuce looks so healthy and full!
And that shade of green, look at that.
I mean, this calls for more lettuce, a cool bath, and more pets! Come in!

[tootroot], what are those!?
These peaches are GIANT, how did you make them?
What a beautiful shade they both are.
I don’t know what shocked me more, the tree yesterday or the peaches today!
Well, we gotta get you in here for some more peaches and a cool bath, right?
So many beautiful tomatoes! That’s crazy, how did you make so many in such a short time?
I saw you yesterday! All of these were made within a day!
Come on in, and bring that garden on your back! I’ll get you some more tomatoes and I’ll draw a cool bath for you.
I’m glad I got to see all your hard work before…who knows what.

I’m getting fired, [tootroot], and I won’t be living here anymore.
I don’t even know if I’ll be in Ventreville for much longer.
So, I’m glad I saw you do so well.
Come here, let me give you all the pets I can.

If I can manage to stay here, I’m glad I know where I can find you!
I’ll see you with the kids.
But you’ll always be [tootroot] to me, not “Tooty.”
Do you want me to try your crop?

Wow, I’d be honored.
Thank you!
I’m sure it’s going to be amazing.
Oh, that energy! I didn’t realize it would rejuvenate so fast.
Apothecaries use your crops, right? I can see why!
But I think our time is up, right?
[color=#ffed29](At this hour? Do I really want to see anyone now?)
My goodness, you’ve grown quite a couple of inches in the last day!
[color=#ffed29](This must be how my Gramma felt when I was in high school.)
And honestly, of all the visitors to show up, I’m glad it was you.
I’ll get you some more lettuce, and I’ll get a cool bath going too!
Um, I knew Tootroots grew quickly, but this is crazy, [tootroot]!
I mean, I was hoping you’d grow a peach, but I was clearly not prepared for what that would actually entail.
Honestly, I didn’t really want visitors today, but you’re the exception.
I gotta get you some good food and a cool bath to support that ecosystem you got on your back!
Is this the same [tootroot] that I knew? I can’t see her under all these leaves!
This is awesome, you look like you’re ready for dozens of tomatoes.
Well I hope your hard work pays off…
Sorry, I’m not in the best mood right now.
Wasn’t sure if I wanted to see anyone tonight, but you are always the exception.
But come in, come in! I’ll get you some more tomatoes, draw a cool bath, and I’ll be sure to get some good scratches in, too.
I’m glad you don’t have to deal with office politics, or bad bosses.
You do what you do, and you do it well.
Plus, your crops help people! They’re used by apothecaries, right?
They boost energy, help with stomach stuff…
You sure you can’t cure the [b]Devil’s Lung[/b]?
What am I going to do, [tootroot]...go back to Germanon?
I’ll miss you. I’ll miss Herb and Mrs. Langtree.
Oh my gosh, and I’ll definitely miss Blight and Rondeau.

Thanks for visiting me before everything goes down.
Love you.

[color=#ffed29](Gramma’s gonna be furious…)
[color=#ffed29](I’ll have to talk her down from coming to Ventreville and whooping Mr. Gungand right here right now.)
My dear Orven, lovely to hear from you.

Doesn’t make it any less lovely!
How are you feeling? I know things were a bit rough last night.

And what for???
I know MY SON has done NOTHING but his BEST.

FOR NOTHING, GRAMMA.
YOU [i]KNOW[/i] I’VE DONE NOTHING WRONG.
I know and I believe it!

YEP.
Gramma, I knew he didn’t like me, but to have it OUT FOR ME like this???

This is discrimination!
It’s ILLEGAL.
And I’m about to go over there to deal some justice of MY OWN.
Gramma, don’t worry, I’m okay here.

But this Gungand fellow won’t be okay soon!
Not if I have anything to say!!!
You swear to me, you've done nothing wrong, and I’ll come right here with my good cane, and you’ll never hear from him again.

I swear it!
And you know what…I wish I did MORE.
Knowing they’d be like this, I wish I just would’ve stuck with my gut the whole time and did what was right.
Then give me three days, and you’re gonna be fine.

[i]Haha[/i], nah, Gramma, he’s not worth it.
When you come over, I wanna show you all around the city and we’ll both have a great time.

I’ll have a great time!
A certain someone else won’t, but I certainly will!

Gramma, seriously, I’m fine.
I’m just frustrated.
I called some friends and they said I should bring it up to Mister Avidine.
A great idea! If he’s worth a can of beans, he’ll stop this.

Call me after work tomorrow…
I’ll be praying for you.
Thank you, Gramma, it might be an earlier call.
My line for you is 24/7—call me anytime.
Love you, too, my brave and wonderful Orven.
